rComments: I had her for my online George Brown College "Aborig. Edu." course. The annoying thing about the course is that we have to go out to an Aborig. event and write a 40% worth report on it. I fell behind about nine weeks in the course and she let me do late assignments (when they were technically worth nothing). Be nice and suck up to her!
Very easy to get good marks

Erica believes in respect for people. If you respect her, she will respect you. She is concerned about student performance and explains concepts pretty well. However there is no visual aid such as powerpoints etc. These could be added along with class debates and videos to make it more interesting. she can be a little intimidating and harsh

She reads directly out of the book, has no class activities or assignments, no powerpoint/visual aid, and if she runs out of things to say she will either end class early or ask the class to talk aimlessly. Even the paper that we have to write has no topic or even an outline! Easiest class in the world because she's completely clueless!
Incredible, very respectful and knows her stuff. Do your part and she has no problem. Will highly recommend a class with her.
